The following starting materials were prepared by chiral catalytic hydrogenation of their corresponding 3,4-dihydroisoquinolines by a procedure similar to that described by Noyori et al. (
  
    Uematsu, N.; Fujii, A.; Hashiguchi, S.; Ikariya, T.; Noyori, R. J. Am. Chem. Soc. 1996, 118, 4916-4917
  ) followed by 
  N-methylation: 
  

(1R)-6,7-Dimethoxy-2-methyl-1-(3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline;

(1S)-6,7-Dimethoxy-2-methyl-1-(3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline.
